  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight by linking the discovered failures to the internal state of the model at the time of failure. In two of the main experiments, the authors go beyond simply reporting a failure and inspect the model to explain the mechanism. For instance, when finding numerical errors (NaNs), they identify that the cause is one logit having a very positive value and another having a very negative value. When finding a bug in a GAN implementation, they diagnose the problem as the discriminator's output having too high a magnitude, causing saturated gradients. This level of analysis connects failures to model internals (logits, gradients), which fits the 'Medium' criteria. However, it does not extend to explaining the underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., what features in the input cause these extreme internal states), which would be required for a 'High' rating.",
